What is an Operator?

An Operator is a custom controller that automates the management of complex, stateful applications on Kubernetes.

You create a Custom Resource (CR)
        ↓
Operator watches for it
        ↓
Operator takes action (like a human DBA would)
        ↓
Operator keeps reconciling to match desired state


Operator = CRD + Custom Controller

CRD (Custom Resource Definition)
→ defines the new object type (e.g. MySQLCluster)

Custom Controller
→ watches for that object and acts on it

Together = Operator

what statefullset in k8s 

The Operator then automatically:

Creates StatefulSets
Sets up replication between instances
Handles failover
Takes backups
Manages config 
